<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>take a shine to someone • take the shine out of someone</xh5><p> <i>take a shine to someone</i>—(coll.) take a fancy to a person; develop a liking for smb.: I suppose I oughtn’t to blame you if Marion’s <u>taken a shine to</u> you. You must have a way with women.</p><p> <i>take the shine out of someone</i>—(coll.) deprive smb. of his supremacy; surpass a person <i>(also: take the shine off someone):</i> That girl’s got it in her, I can tell you. She’ll <u>take the shine out of</u> some of our West-Enders.</p> </entry>
